# Plan: Custom Named Color Theme System

## Context

T3 Code currently has a minimal light/dark/system toggle (`hooks/useTheme.ts`) that only flips a `.dark` class on `<html>`. The task adds a richer named-theme system ("t3-dark", "t3-light", "t3-midnight") with explicit surface-specific color tokens (sidebar, editor, terminal, status bar), a React ThemeProvider, a `useTheme` hook backed by localStorage, CSS custom property application, and a visual theme selector with preview swatches.

The three new themes directly replace the old "light | dark | system" selector.

---

## Files to Create

### 1. `packages/contracts/src/theme.ts`
Type definitions only — no runtime data. Follows the exact `editor.ts` pattern (plain `as const` array + `Schema.Literals`):

```ts
import { Schema } from "effect";

export const THEME_IDS = ["t3-dark", "t3-light", "t3-midnight"] as const;

export const ThemeId = Schema.Literals(THEME_IDS);
export type ThemeId = typeof ThemeId.Type;

export interface ThemeColorTokens {
  background: string;
  foreground: string;
  card: string; cardForeground: string;
  popover: string; popoverForeground: string;
  primary: string; primaryForeground: string;
  secondary: string; secondaryForeground: string;
  muted: string; mutedForeground: string;
  accent: string; accentForeground: string;
  destructive: string; destructiveForeground: string;
  border: string; input: string; ring: string;
  // Extended surface tokens (new CSS vars: --sidebar, --editor, --terminal, --status-bar)
  sidebar: string; sidebarForeground: string; sidebarBorder: string;
  editor: string; editorForeground: string;
  terminal: string; terminalForeground: string;
  statusBar: string; statusBarForeground: string;
}

export interface ThemeDefinition {
  id: ThemeId;
  label: string;
  isDark: boolean; // whether to apply `.dark` class for Tailwind dark: variants
  tokens: ThemeColorTokens;
}
```

---

### 2. `apps/web/src/themes.ts`
Runtime theme data — three `ThemeDefinition` objects and lookup helpers. Imported only by the web app.

Color values for the three themes:

**`t3-dark`** — existing dark palette translated to explicit tokens:
- bg: `color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-neutral-950) 95%, var(--color-white))`
- fg: `var(--color-neutral-100)`, primary: `oklch(0.588 0.217 264)`
- sidebar slightly darker, editor slightly lighter than bg, terminal: `var(--color-neutral-950)`
- statusBar: `oklch(0.28 0.05 264)` (dark purple-blue strip), `isDark: true`

**`t3-light`** — existing light palette translated:
- bg: `var(--color-white)`, fg: `var(--color-neutral-800)`, primary: `oklch(0.488 0.217 264)`
- sidebar: `var(--color-neutral-50)`, editor: `var(--color-neutral-50)`
- terminal: `var(--color-neutral-100)`, statusBar: `oklch(0.488 0.217 264)` (primary colored)
- `isDark: false`

**`t3-midnight`** — new deep indigo-black theme:
- bg: `oklch(0.11 0.03 264)`, fg: `oklch(0.93 0.01 264)`, primary: `oklch(0.65 0.22 264)`
- sidebar: `oklch(0.095 0.025 264)`, editor: `oklch(0.1 0.028 264)`
- terminal: `oklch(0.085 0.02 264)`, statusBar: `oklch(0.17 0.06 264)`
- All muted/accent/secondary tokens use `--alpha(oklch(0.65 0.22 264) / 8-14%)` for purple tinting
- `isDark: true`

Exports:
```ts
